-  Eat healthy: Choose foods that are good for your heart. Focus on fruits, vegetables, whole grains, and lean proteins. Limit fatty meats, fried foods, and processed snacks.

-  Get moving: Stay active by engaging in regular physical activity. Aim for at least 30 minutes of exercise most days of the week. Walking, cycling, or dancing are great options.

-  Maintain a healthy weight: Strive to achieve a healthy weight through a balanced diet and regular exercise. Losing excess weight can help improve cholesterol levels.